      <div class="start-content text-justify separate-bottom">
        <p>
          “Symbiosis” attempts to connect the visual and culturally 
          familiar experience of a landscape, so that the viewer can 
          identify with the pleasure of existing and also become aware of 
          issues that imperil our fragile earth. By employing the human 
          figure within these landscapes, a symbiotic relationship is 
          formed. The landscapes chosen are protected and serve as a means
          to preserve the area’s ecology.
        </p>
        <p>
          “Humility”, “Introspection” and “Paha” were shot in Lençóis 
          Maranhenses National Park in Maranhão, Brazil. It is 155 hectare
          oasis, full of high dunes up to 40 feet tall and freshwater 
          ponds, whose waters range from shades of green and blue.
        </p>
        <p>
          “Speciation”, “Capsized”, “Obligate” were shot on the beaches of
          Play Grande, Costa Rica, home to Parque Nacional Marino Las 
          Baulas, the nesting ground of the largest marine reptile, the 
          Leatherback Turtle. The continued survival of the Leatherback 
          Seaturtle depends upon the preservation of Costa Rica’s beaches 
          including Playa Grande. For more information please visit 
          seaturtles.org
        </p>
